OL,3,CWill Labour rip up the rules on Right
OL,4,Cto Buy to protect council homes?
OL,6,F"We currently have 1.4 million people
OL,7,Fwaiting for a social home, we've got
OL,8,F159,000 homeless kids in England and
OL,9,Fthat's up about 8,000 since March this
OL,10,Fyear.
OL,12,F"And we've got far too many people
OL,13,Fwithout the ability to access safe and
OL,14,Fdecent social housing."
OL,16,FUnder Right to Buy tenants can buy the
OL,17,Fcouncil home they rent from the local
OL,18,Fauthority at a discount. Residents can
OL,19,Fonly apply after three years and after
OL,20,Ffive years discounts increase for each
OL,21,Fyear they are a tenant.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G9/14
